# <type>(<scope>): <imperative summary>
#
# @see docs/specs/400-dx-conventions/spec.md [FR-5] [FR-7] [FR-11]
# @see docs/specs/400-dx-conventions/design.md [DES-ARCH]
#
# Setup once: git config commit.template .gitmessage
#
# Types:
#   build | chore | ci | docs | feat | fix | perf | refactor | revert | style | test
#
# Scopes are required and commitlint-enforced. Common scopes:
#   agent | chat | docs | dx | infra | pi | pi-sdk | repo | shared | spec
#   transport | ui | vscode | workbench | workbench/notes | workbench/pipeline
#
# Header selection:
#   feat(chat): user/runtime-visible feature
#   fix(vscode): bug fix
#   docs(spec): living spec/design/tasks only
#   docs(dx): convention or documentation workflow change
#   refactor(shared): behavior-preserving source change
#   test(pi): tests only
#   chore(deps): dependency/generated/vendor maintenance
#
# Body for non-trivial commits:
#
# Why:
# - What problem this solves.
#
# Changed:
# - What changed, grouped by surface.
#
# Spec:
# - docs/specs/XXX-name/spec.md [FR-X]
# - docs/specs/XXX-name/design.md [DES-X]
#
# Traceability:
# - @see retargeting, map IDs, generated artifacts, or none.
#
# Verification:
# - pnpm verify
#
# Footer:
# Co-Authored-By: Name <email>
# BREAKING CHANGE: description
#
# Breaking change: add ! after scope, or add BREAKING CHANGE: footer.
